{"parse":{"title":"Multicultural particularism","pageid":21084397,"revid":263943523,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Multicultural particularism</b> is the belief that a common culture for all people is either undesirable or impossible.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> In discussions of <a href=\"/wiki/Multiculturalism\" title=\"Multiculturalism\">multiculturalism</a>, historian and educator <a href=\"/wiki/Diane_Ravitch\" title=\"Diane Ravitch\">Diane Ravitch</a> draws a distinction between what she terms \"pluralistic\" and \"particularistic\" varieties. Other writers often blur or ignore this distinction; it is often difficult to discern whether advocacy for \"<a href=\"/wiki/Multiculturalism\" title=\"Multiculturalism\">diversity</a>\" or \"<a href=\"/wiki/Multiculturalism\" title=\"Multiculturalism\">multiculturalism</a>\" is intended to promote particularism or not. In some quarters, even to raise the issue is <a href=\"/wiki/Taboo\" title=\"Taboo\">taboo</a>.\n</p><p>In a long essay about multiculturalism in American education, Ravitch praises the inclusiveness of multicultural pluralism while decrying what she says as multiple flaws and failures of multicultural particularism.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Multicultural_particularism&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Asham bin Ahmad (August 22, 2006). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ikim.gov.my/v5/print.php?grp=2&amp;key=1096\">\"Debunking Multiculturalism\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">January 13,</span> 2008</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Debunking+Multiculturalism&amp;rft.date=2006-08-22&amp;rft.au=Asham+bin+Ahmad&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ikim.gov.my%2Fv5%2Fprint.php%3Fgrp%3D2%26key%3D1096&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMulticultural+particularism\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://college.hmco.com/currentconflict/students/multicultural/ravitch_article/intro.html\">\"Houghton Mifflin\"</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Houghton+Mifflin&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcollege.hmco.com%2Fcurrentconflict%2Fstudents%2Fmulticultural%2Fravitch_article%2Fintro.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMulticultural+particularism\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Vista_Login_Manager_Cropped.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/15/Vista_Login_Manager_Cropped.svg/40px-Vista_Login_Manager_Cropped.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/15/Vista_Login_Manager_Cropped.svg/60px-Vista_Login_Manager_Cropped.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wi